section.section:
The Board shall issue a license to an individual who is on inactive status if the individual is otherwise entitled to be licensed under this title and submits to the Board:
Satisfactory evidence of compliance with the continuing education requirements the Board adopts for this purpose;
A reinstatement fee set by the Board;
A licensure affidavit;
Federation of boards certification of good standing;
The response to an inquiry to the national Healthcare Integrity and Protection Data Bank;
History of malpractice cases;
Proof of out-of-state practice preceding the request for reinstatement that is sufficient to demonstrate current clinical proficiency, as specified in regulations adopted by the Board; and
Proof of passing the Ethics-Jurisprudence Examination as administered by the Board within the last licensing cycle preceding the individual's reinstatement application.
